---
<BaseLayout title="Coding Agent — Codebolt" navbarVariant="solid" site={site} navigation={navigation}>
  <PageHeader
    title="A coding agent that can grow past the chat window."
    subtitle="Use Codebolt as a serious software agent for coding, review, tests, refactors, repositories, terminals, and multi-agent development work."
  />
  <CenteredText
    variant="thesis"
    text="Codebolt can start like a familiar coding agent: ask for a change, inspect the repo, edit files, run commands, and review output. The difference is that the same work can continue across CLI, Editor, Cloud, and custom agents without changing engines."
  />
  <CardGrid
    heading="Coding workflows"
    cards={[{"title":"Repository-aware implementation","body":"Agents can inspect files, follow project conventions, edit code, run tests, and iterate until the change is coherent. Use the CLI for terminal-first work or the Editor for a visual coding surface.","visual":"inspect repo\npatch files\nrun tests\nexplain result\n"},{"title":"Parallel coding threads","body":"Run multiple coding tasks at once instead of one linear chat. Split exploration, implementation, review, docs, and verification across agent threads.","visual":"thread 1 → frontend\nthread 2 → backend\nthread 3 → tests\nthread 4 → docs\n"},{"title":"Review and merge loops","body":"Agents can review each other's work, identify conflicts, run checks, and prepare changes for merge. Codebolt is built for agent teams, not only individual chat sessions.","visual":"agent A implements\nagent B reviews\nagent C tests\nmerge when ready\n"}]}
  />
  <FeatureBlock
    heading="Same coding state across surfaces"
    body="Start in the Editor, continue in the CLI, push a long-running job to Cloud, or turn a repeated coding workflow into a custom agent. The engine remains the same, so the context, memory, tools, and plugins can carry forward."
    reverse={true}
    diagram="Editor ↔ CLI ↔ Cloud
   ↘      ↓      ↙
    Codebolt engine
       memory
       agents
       plugins
       environments
"
  />
  <CtaBlock
    heading="Use Codebolt as your coding agent."
    buttons={[{"label":"Download Codebolt","href":"/download","variant":"primary"},{"label":"Explore CLI","href":"/products/cli","variant":"secondary"}]}
  />
</BaseLayout>
